The paper focuses on developing a personalized recommender system for improving subjective wellbeing by aligning daily activities with personality traits. This involves leveraging mobile technologies and user modeling. The paper also uses a rich dataset collected in a smartphone study. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Cybernetics (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
